---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="NAVAN Symbol" description="The first public Vaelinya symbol: NAVAN, Remember.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Artefacts · Symbols</p>
    <h1>NAVAN — Remember</h1>
    <p class="lede">NAVAN is the first public Vaelinya symbol-word. It means “Remember.”</p>

    <article class="visual-callout visual-callout-artefacts">
      <div class="visual-callout-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span>Na</span></div>
      <div class="visual-callout-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Visual description</p>
        <h2>A mark for memory and witness</h2>
        <p>The public mark is a simple circular sign holding the sound-shape “Na.” It stands for remembrance, careful attention, and the choice to keep truth alive.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Meaning</p>
      <h2>What NAVAN does in the world</h2>
      <p>NAVAN connects language, story, and artefact. It is used when someone needs to remember a person, a place, a promise, or a truth that could otherwise be lost.</p>
      <p>It is not only a word. It is a small act of witness: a way to say that something still matters, even when time, fear, distance, or noise tries to cover it.</p>
      <div class="link-list">
        <a href="/language/lexicon/">Find NAVAN in the lexicon</a>
        <a href="/world/the-warm-remembering/">Follow the Warm Remembering</a>
        <a href="/read/lina/">Read Lina’s stories</a>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Accessibility note</p>
      <h2>The symbol is not image-only</h2>
      <p>The essential meaning of NAVAN is available in text on this page. The mark supports the meaning, but the meaning does not depend on sight alone.</p>
    </article>

    <p><a class="button secondary" href="/artefacts/symbols/">Back to symbols</a></p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
